quran[67]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,Nay! I swear by this city
  90,2,And you are free in this city
  90,3,And by the begetter and that which he begot
  90,4,"Verily, We have created man in Kabad"
  90,5,Does he think that none can overcome him
  90,6,"He says: \"I have wasted wealth in abundance"
  90,7,Does he think that none sees him
  90,8,Have We not made for him two eyes
  90,9,And a tongue and two lips
  90,10,And shown him the two ways
  90,11,But he has not attempted to pass on the path that is steep
  90,12,And what will make you know the path that is steep
  90,13,Freeing a neck
  90,14,Or giving food in a day full of Masghabah
  90,15,To an orphan near of kin
  90,16,Or to a Miskin cleaving to dust
  90,17,"Then he became one of those who believed and recommended one another to patience, and recommended one another to compassion"
  90,18,They are those on the Right
  90,19,"But those who disbelieved in Our Ayat, they are those on the Left"
  90,20,Upon them Fire will Mu'sadah
  91,1,By the sun and Duhaha
  91,2,By the moon as it Talaha
  91,3,By the day as it Jallaha
  91,4,By the night as it Yaghshaha
  91,5,By the heaven and Ma Banaha
  91,6,By the earth and Ma Tahhaha
  91,7,"By Nafs, and Ma Sawwaha (Who apportioned it)"
  91,8,Then He showed it its Fujur and its Taqwa
  91,9,Indeed he succeeds who purifies it
  91,10,And indeed he fails who Dassaha
  91,11,Thamud denied through their trans- gression
  91,12,When their most wicked went forth
  91,13,"But the Messenger of Allah said to them: \"Be cautious! That is the she-camel of Allah! (Do not harm it) and (bar it not from having) its drink"
  91,14,"Then they denied him and they killed it. So their Lord destroyed them because of their sin, Fasawwaha"
  91,15,And He feared not the consequences thereof
  92,1,By the night as it envelops
  92,2,By the day as it appears
  92,3,By Him Who created male and female
  92,4,"Certainly, your efforts and deeds are diverse"
  92,5,As for him who gives and has Taqwa
  92,6,And believes in Al-Husna
  92,7,We will make smooth for him the path of ease
  92,8,But he who is greedy and thinks himself self-sufficient
  92,9,And denies Al-Husna
  92,10,We will make smooth for him the path to evil
  92,11,And what will his wealth avail him when he goes down (in destruction)
  92,12,"Truly, on Us is (to give) guidance"
  92,13,"And truly, unto Us (belong) the last (Hereafter) and the first (this world)"
  92,14,Therefore I have warned you of a Fire Talazza
  92,15,None shall enter it save the most wretched
  92,16,Who denies and turns away
  92,17,And those with Taqwa will be far removed from it
  92,18,He who gives of his wealth for self-purification
  92,19,And who has (in mind) no favor from anyone to be paid back
  92,20,"Except to seek the Face of his Lord, the Most High"
  92,21,"He, surely, will be pleased"
  93,1,By the forenoon
  93,2,By the night when it darkens
  93,3,Your Lord has neither forsaken you nor hates you
  93,4,And indeed the Hereafter is better for you than the present
  93,5,"And verily, your Lord will give you so that you shall be well-pleased"
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan and gave you a refuge
  93,7,And He found you unaware and guided you
  93,8,And He found you poor and made you rich
  93,9,"Therefore, treat not the orphan with oppression"
  93,10,And repulse not the one who asks
  93,11,And proclaim the grace of your Lord